Absenteeism at work.

Absenteeism is defined as absence to work as expected, represents for the company the loss of productivity and quality of work. Workers in the factory are absent from work for various reasons. My client is Hanh Nong, who is the head of a factory belonging to a Cosmetic Company that produces cosmetic products. She has a couple of questions:

Question 1: What is the most impacting reason for the workers to be absent? Question 2: Is there a relation between age and the number of absent hours of the worker?

From these questions, the client would like to assertain if there can be policy changes in the company that can help workers and reduce the number of absent hours.

The data has many numeric values. These values are not useful in the visualizations and do not make for readable visualizations for the client. I modified these visualizations into understandable values which makes it easier for me and the client to read and understand.

Data Explorations: Below are some data explorations from the data, there are significantly more number of people in the dataset with lesser number of pets and kids.

The dataset also contains many people that do not drink. When we potetially run regression and include these in the independent variables, it will potentially skew the results as the model has lesser values of people who drink.

The distributions below shows the distributions of days of week in the dataset.

The visualization below show the reasons for workers to be absent. The top reason for the worker to be absent seems to be medical consultation. The max number of reasons for the workers to be absent seems to be health related. Can we say that the workers might be stressed? The client can make sure the workers are not stressed by organising events that can help in team building along with being enjoyable. This can help motivate the workers to come to work.

The below graph shows the relation of various age groups with the total number of absent hours. The graph shows that people in the age group of 34 have the highest number of absent hours. In this age groups, we can also see if the people in the group on an average are social drinkers or not. This data could potentially be useful when considering the exceptions that the workers could have that could motivate them to come to work. We can also assume that people tend be absent from work after a night out. If we can give the employees the option of working from home, maybe they would be motivated to come to work. The width of the bins represent the number of people in that age group. This data could be useful if we are using this variable for a regression or analysis in the future. We can see that we have max number of people in age group of 34 and 55. This could overfit the results of the regression and skew the results.
